examples.en: I like all sorts of food - I'm not fussy.
She owns all sorts of property around town.
He prepared all sorts of yummy dishes.
He did all sorts of jobs to earn a living.
They sailed through all sorts of contradictions.
I had a conversation of sorts with a very drunk man at the bus stop.
She called me all sorts of carrion names.
These sorts of birds live in more wooded areas.
I have not fruited those sorts of strawberries.
The Egyptians mummied all sorts of sacred brutes.
Rex did all sorts of tricks. I cried when he died.
They play pop, rock, jazz, soul, all sorts in there.
People were flinging all sorts of accusations at her.
Louise went back to work feeling rather out of sorts.
They stuffed their suitcases with all sorts of things.
He has wide acquaintanceship among all sorts of people.
He was imagining all sorts of terrible things happening.
There were all sorts of rumours buzzing through the office.
He told us all sorts of humorous anecdotes about his childhood.
She's made all sorts of wild accusations against me in the past.
The competition gives you the chance to win all sorts of goodies.
They sell all sorts of weird and wonderful (=very strange) products.
The weight of evidence is that unemployment leads to all sorts of health problems.
The doctor has doped me up with all sorts of medicine to try to control the fever.
We have relationships of many different sorts - with our children, our parents, our boss and our friends, to name but a few.
